hopobject.body: Have you got a current driving licence? aps phenadrine v2 For years, many physicians have given regular chest X-rays for patients who are current or former smokers, even though chest X-rays have never been shown to be effective at detecting lung cancer, Smith says. More recently some doctors have started screening their high-risk patients with LDCT, Smith says. The new guidelines say clearly to abandon chest X-rays altogether for lung cancer screening and use only LDCT, he says.
